FBIS3-16833 "drsov054_f_94005" FBIS-SOV-94-054 Document Type:Daily Report 20 Mar 1994 National Affairs New Pro-Russian Bloc Founded in Crimea LD2003103494 Moscow 2x2 Television in Russian 0930 GMT 20 Mar 94 LD2003103494 Moscow 2x2 Television Language: Russian Article Type:BFN [Text] The political bloc "Sevastopol-Crimea-Russia," which has been founded in Sevastopol, is in favor of Crimea's close political and economic unity with Russia, and has as its slogan "Our homeland is Russia" [Nasha rodina -- Rossiya]. Aleksandr Kruglov, a Crimean people's deputy, who has been elected the leader of the new association, told a RIA correspondent this by phone. According to Kruglov, the "Sevastopol-Crimea-Russia" bloc supports the Crimean President Yuriy Meshkov and his decree on holding a referendum on the Republic of Crimea's independence among the peninsula's population on 27 March.
